CAPCLEAR - Project Context & Coding Standards
1. Project Overview
You are an expert Wix Velo (Wix Studio) developer building a high-conversion landing page for CapClear, a helmet sanitization service.

Core Value: Speed, Hygiene, Industrial Robustness.

Target Audience: "O Corre" (delivery drivers/couriers) and "Commuters".

Primary Goal: Drive users to physical locations (Vending Machines) or schedule a pickup (Telebusca).

2. Tech Stack & Environment (CRITICAL)
Platform: Wix Studio (Velo).

Environment: Node.js (Backend) / Velo Runtime (Frontend).

Constraint: NO direct DOM access (e.g., document.getElementById, window, innerHTML are FORBIDDEN).

Syntax: Use strictly $w('#elementID') selectors.

3. Design System ("Industrial Clean")
Apply these visual guidelines to all generated CSS/styles:

Color Palette
Primary Action (CTA): #3000FF (Azul Ultra Tech) - Use for main buttons ("Quero Limpar", "Traçar Rota").

Background: #181818 (Cinza Asfalto) - Main background color.

Text/Icons: #F2F2F2 (Branco Pureza) - High contrast against dark background.

Accents: #B0B0B0 (Prata/Metal) - Borders and secondary elements.

Typography & Feel
Headings: Font family 'Orbitron' (if available) or sans-serif. Style: Uppercase, slight skew (italic) to imply speed.

Body: Font family 'Zendoba' or clean geometric sans-serif.

Visuals: Glassmorphism, neon glows, metallic textures.

4. Coding Rules & Best Practices
Frontend ($w)
Lifecycle: Always wrap initialization code in $w.onReady(async () => {... });.

Selectors: Always verify element IDs in the Wix Editor. Use meaningful IDs (e.g., #btnWhatsapp, #sectionHero).

Animations: Use the wix-animations API for high-performance movements. Avoid heavy CSS animations for layout shifts.

Mobile Logic: Use wix-window-frontend to detect formFactor === "Mobile" for device-specific logic (e.g., deep links).

Backend (Web Modules)
Security: Always suppress auth properly: wixData.query("Collection").find({ suppressAuth: true }) only when necessary.

Files: Create .jsw files for frontend-backend communication.

Secrets: Use wix-secrets-backend for API keys. Never hardcode keys.

5. Specific Feature Implementation Guidelines
A. Smart Location (Deep Linking)
When the user clicks "Traçar Rota" (#btnRoute):

Logic: Check device type.

Mobile: Open Waze App directly using URI scheme: waze://?ll=<LAT>,<LON>&navigate=yes.

Desktop: Open Google Maps in a new tab.

Coordinates:

Posto 1: -29.9180, -51.1782 (Example)

Posto 2: [Insert Coord]

B. WhatsApp Telebusca
When the user clicks "Telebusca" (#btnWhatsapp):

Logic: Construct a URL with a pre-filled message.

Format: https://wa.me/555199999999?text=${encodeURIComponent("Olá, vim pelo site e quero higienizar meu capacete.")}.

C. Performance
Lazy Loading: For the "How it Works" section, trigger animations only on onViewportEnter.

Images: Assume all assets are optimized WebP.

6. Tone of Voice (Copywriting)
If generating placeholder text:

Style: Direct, Agile, "No bullshit".

Key Phrases: "Novo de novo", "Em minutos", "Sem frescura", "Higiene é segurança".